# Tailwind & Theming

## Theme Colors

Use semantic color tokens from `@theme` in `src/index.css`, not raw Tailwind colors:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw colors bypass theming
className="text-gray-400 bg-gray-900"

// ✅ GOOD — semantic tokens
className="text-text-faint bg-base"
```

Type accent colors: `accent-green` (string), `accent-blue` (number), `accent-peach` (boolean), `text-text-faint` (null), `accent-mauve` (object), `accent-yellow` (array).

## Dark/Light Mode

The current pattern uses `isDark ? X : Y` ternaries. When refactoring to `@custom-variant dark`, use a single class that auto-resolves:

```tsx
// Current (acceptable until refactored)
className={isDark ? 'bg-base text-text-primary' : 'bg-base-light text-text-light'}

// Target (after @custom-variant migration)
className="bg-base text-text-primary"
```

## Class Organization

Order utility classes: layout → spacing → typography → colors → effects → modifiers.

Keep component-specific classes inline. Extract to CSS only for complex animations or pseudo-elements.

## New Components

Match existing visual patterns: `text-[11px] font-mono` for data, `text-[10px] tracking-widest uppercase` for labels, `text-xs` for UI text. Border color: `border-border` (dark) / `border-border-light` (light).
